text: Sandy Baltimore (born 19 February 2000) is a French professional footballer who plays as a forward for Division 1 Féminine club Paris Saint-Germain. ==Early life== Baltimore began playing football at the age of 10. She is of Guadeloupean origin. ==Career== A youth academy graduate of Paris Saint- Germain, Baltimore made her professional debut on 9 October 2016, replacing Hawa Cissoko in a 3–0 league win against Metz. In April 2018, scored a brace during the team's 4–0 win against OM Feminines during the Women's Classico. It was just Baltimore's eighth league match, and her fourth start, for PSG during the 2017–18 season. She signed her first professional contract with PSG at the end of the season, after helping the club win the 2017–18 Coupe de France. Baltimore is a French youth international and was part of the France under-19 squad which won 2019 UEFA Championship.
